{
  "To demonstrate it, let's say we were building a carousel like experience whose content was different Pokémon from the <a href=\"https://pokeapi.co/\" metastring=\"\">PokéAPI</a>.": "为了演示，假设我们要做一个类似轮播的体验，内容是来自 <a href=\"https://pokeapi.co/\" metastring=\"\">PokéAPI</a> 的不同宝可梦。",
  "We know based on <button aria-controls=\"radix-:rlr:\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>Rule #0</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button> that we need to keep our network request out of React's rendering flow. Now we just need to decide <strong metastring=\"\">where</strong> we put it, either in an event handler or in <code>useEffect</code>.": "根据 <button aria-controls=\"\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>Rule #0</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button>，我们知道必须把网络请求放在 React 的渲染流程之外。剩下要决定的只是把它放在<strong metastring=\"\">哪里</strong> —— 是放在事件处理函数里，还是 <code>useEffect</code> 里。",
  "This becomes obvious when we break it down further. What exactly does <em metastring=\"\">\"whenever the user interacts with our carousel\"</em> actually mean? When they click a button? What about navigating with their keyboard? What if we wanted our carousel to change Pokemon automatically every few seconds? What about on the initial render when there's no user interaction but we still need to fetch the first Pokémon?": "再拆细就会一目了然。<em metastring=\"\">“每当用户和轮播交互时”</em>到底是什么意思？点击按钮？用键盘翻页？那如果我们希望轮播每隔几秒就自动切换呢？或者首次渲染时其实并没有用户交互，但我们也需要拉取第一只宝可梦？",
  "The take away here is there's no single event that should trigger our network request. Instead, what we're really wanting to do is <em metastring=\"\">synchronize</em> our component with the result of calling the Pokémon API – the perfect use case for <code>useEffect</code>.": "核心结论是：没有哪一个单独的事件应该来触发我们的网络请求。我们真正想做的，是把组件和调用 Pokémon API 的结果<em metastring=\"\">同步</em>起来 —— 这正是 <code>useEffect</code> 最合适的场景。",
  "Before we worry the async bits, let's build out the basic logic for our carousel first. Again, the entire premise of this app is to synchronize our component with the result of calling the Pokémon API. To do that, we'll need some state. Specifically, we'll add an <code>id</code> state to keep track of the <code>id</code> of the Pokémon we're currently viewing and a <code>pokemon</code> state to keep track of the actual Pokémon data. Our <code>id</code> state will default to <code>1</code> since that's the <code>id</code> of the first Pokémon, Bulbasaur.": "在处理异步之前，我们先把轮播的基本逻辑搭起来。再强调一次，这个应用的整个前提就是把组件与 Pokémon API 的结果同步起来。为此我们需要一些 state，具体来说是一个 <code>id</code> state（记录当前查看的宝可梦 id），和一个 <code>pokemon</code> state（记录宝可梦数据本身）。<code>id</code> 的默认值设为 <code>1</code>，因为第一只宝可梦 Bulbasaur 的 <code>id</code> 就是 <code>1</code>。",
  "We'll then encapsulate the async logic for fetching a Pokémon into a function called <code>fetchPokemon</code>. Now, whenever we invoke <code>fetchPokemon</code> passing it an <code>id</code> of the Pokémon we want to fetch, we'll get back an object with an <code>error</code> if there was one or a <code>response</code> of the Pokémon data if there wasn't.": "然后我们把“获取一只宝可梦”的异步逻辑封装进一个叫 <code>fetchPokemon</code> 的函数。每次调用 <code>fetchPokemon</code> 并传入想要获取的宝可梦的 <code>id</code>，我们得到的要么是一个带 <code>error</code> 的对象（若出错），要么是带 <code>response</code>（宝可梦数据）的对象。",
  "Now the fun part. We want to synchronize our local <code>pokemon</code> state with the PokéAPI according to our local <code>id</code> state. That's a fancy way of saying whenever our local <code>id</code> state changes, we want to invoke <code>fetchPokemon</code> passing it the new <code>id</code>. We'll do that by calling <code>fetchPokemon</code> inside of <code>useEffect</code> and then updating our <code>pokemon</code> state with the result.": "现在是有意思的部分。我们想根据本地的 <code>id</code> state，把本地的 <code>pokemon</code> state 和 PokéAPI 同步起来。换成大白话：每当 <code>id</code> 发生变化时，就用新的 <code>id</code> 调用 <code>fetchPokemon</code>。做法是在 <code>useEffect</code> 里调用 <code>fetchPokemon</code>，再用结果更新 <code>pokemon</code> state。",
  "First, notice that our dependency array only includes one element, <code>id</code>. Again, this <strong metastring=\"\">isn't</strong> telling React to re-run the effect when <code>id</code> changes (though, that's what happens). Instead, we're giving React an array of all of the dependencies our effect needs to re-synchronize with the outside system. As a <em metastring=\"\">byproduct</em> of that, whenever React sees that <code>id</code> has changed between renders, it will re-run the effect.": "首先，注意依赖数组里只有一个元素 <code>id</code>。再强调一次，这<strong metastring=\"\">并不是</strong>告诉 React “<code>id</code> 变了就重新运行 effect”（虽然实际效果是这样）。我们真正告诉 React 的是：这是 effect 在和外部系统重新同步时需要依赖的所有值。而作为<em metastring=\"\">附带结果</em>，React 发现渲染之间 <code>id</code> 变了，就会重新运行 effect。",
  "Second, you may be wondering why we declared a new <code>handleFetchPokemon</code> function inside of our event. This is purely aesthetic and was done so that we could use <code>async</code>/<code>await</code> inside of <code>useEffect</code>.": "其次，你可能好奇我们为什么在 effect 里又新声明了一个 <code>handleFetchPokemon</code> 函数。这纯粹是为了写法好看 —— 这样我们就可以在 <code>useEffect</code> 里使用 <code>async</code>/<code>await</code>。",
  "First, we'll need to add two new pieces of state to our component, <code>loading</code> and <code>error</code>. Because <code>fetchPokemon</code> is invoked as a result of rendering, including the initial render, we'll initialize <code>loading</code> to <code>true</code> (and <code>error</code> to <code>null</code>).": "首先，我们要给组件加两块新的 state：<code>loading</code> 和 <code>error</code>。因为 <code>fetchPokemon</code> 是作为渲染的结果被调用的（包括首次渲染），所以把 <code>loading</code> 初始化为 <code>true</code>（<code>error</code> 初始化为 <code>null</code>）。",
  "Now we need our effect to manage our new <code>loading</code> and <code>error</code> states. Thankfully our <code>fetchPokemon</code> function makes this easy since it's so explicit if there's an error.": "接下来需要让 effect 来管理新的 <code>loading</code> 和 <code>error</code> state。好在我们的 <code>fetchPokemon</code> 函数把错误情况处理得很明确，所以这件事很容易。",
  "What we'll do is whenever our effects runs, reset <code>loading</code> and <code>error</code> back to their default values before we make the network request. Then, once we get back a response, if there's an error, we'll update <code>error</code>, and if not, we'll update <code>pokemon</code> before setting <code>loading</code> to <code>false</code>.": "我们的做法是：每次 effect 运行时，先把 <code>loading</code> 和 <code>error</code> 重置回默认值，然后再发起网络请求。拿到响应后，如果有错误就更新 <code>error</code>；否则就更新 <code>pokemon</code>，最后把 <code>loading</code> 置为 <code>false</code>。",
  "Don't get freaked out over the multiple, separate invocations of our updater functions (<code>setError</code>, <code>setPokemon</code>, <code>setLoading</code>). Remember, React \"batches\" those together intelligently so there's no wasted renders.": "不要被多次分别调用的 updater 函数（<code>setError</code>、<code>setPokemon</code>、<code>setLoading</code>）吓到。记住，React 会聪明地把它们“合并”处理，不会有多余的渲染。",
  "You could argue at this point the hardest parts are behind us. It appears we've successfully abstracted the arduous async side effect bits into <code>useEffect</code>, and are now synchronizing our component with the PokéAPI.": "可以说到这里最难的部分已经过去了。看起来我们已经成功地把繁琐的异步副作用封装进了 <code>useEffect</code>，并让组件和 PokéAPI 保持同步。",
  "Notice the simplicity of our app now. Because we've told <code>useEffect</code> to synchronize our local <code>pokemon</code> state with the PokéAPI according to <code>id</code>, we've taken what has historically been the most complex part of building a web app, an asynchronous side effect, and made it an implementation detail behind simply updating <code>id</code> via our <code>handlePrevious</code> and <code>handleNext</code> functions.": "看看现在的应用有多简洁。因为我们告诉 <code>useEffect</code> 根据 <code>id</code> 把本地的 <code>pokemon</code> state 和 PokéAPI 同步起来，就把“构建 Web 应用时最复杂的部分 —— 异步副作用”变成了一个实现细节 —— 用户只需通过 <code>handlePrevious</code> 和 <code>handleNext</code> 更新 <code>id</code> 就好。",
  "Now, unfortunately, we're not <em metastring=\"\">quite</em> done yet. As is, our code contains the <em metastring=\"\">worst</em> kind of bug – one that is both inconspicuous and deceptively wasteful. Can you spot it?": "可惜，我们还<em metastring=\"\">没完全</em>搞定。目前的代码里藏着一种<em metastring=\"\">最糟</em>的 bug —— 既不起眼，又暗地里非常浪费资源。你能发现吗？",
  "Whenever we call <code>fetchPokemon</code>, because it's an asynchronous request, we have no idea how long that request will take to resolve. It's completely possible that, while we're in the process of waiting for a response, our Carousel updates <code>id</code>, which causes a re-render, which causes our effect to run again with a different <code>id</code>.": "每次调用 <code>fetchPokemon</code>，因为它是异步请求，我们完全不知道它要多久才能完成。完全有可能在我们等待响应的过程中，轮播更新了 <code>id</code>，从而触发重新渲染，进而让 effect 用一个不同的 <code>id</code> 再次运行。",
  "In this scenario, we now have two requests in flight, both with different <code>id</code>s. Worse, we have no way of knowing which one will resolve first. In both scenarios, we're calling <code>setPokemon</code> when the request resolves. That means, because we don't know in which order they'll resolve, <code>pokemon</code>, and therefor our UI, will eventually be <em metastring=\"\">whatever request was resolved last</em>. To make it worse, you'll also get a flash of the Pokémon that resolves first, before the second one does.": "这时就有两个并行在途的请求，对应两个不同的 <code>id</code>。更糟的是，我们根本没法预测哪个先完成。不管哪个完成，我们都会调用 <code>setPokemon</code>。也就是说，最终 <code>pokemon</code>（以及 UI）会停留在<em metastring=\"\">最后一个完成的请求</em>上。雪上加霜的是：先完成的那只宝可梦还会被短暂地闪一下，然后才被后完成的那一只覆盖掉。",
  "Really what we want to do is to tell React to ignore any responses that come from requests that were made in effects that are no longer relevant. In order to do that, of course, we need a way to know if an effect is the latest one. If not, then we should ignore the response and <strong metastring=\"\">not</strong> <code>setPokemon</code> inside of it.": "我们真正想做的是：让 React 忽略那些来自“已经不再相关”的 effect 所发起请求的响应。要做到这一点，当然需要有办法知道某次 effect 是不是最新的那一次。如果不是最新的，就忽略该响应，<strong metastring=\"\">不再</strong>在它里面调用 <code>setPokemon</code>。",
  "Thankfully, React makes this pretty easy with the last remaining feature of <code>useEffect</code> you haven't seen yet: the \"cleanup\" function.": "好在 React 提供了一个你还没见过的 <code>useEffect</code> 特性让这件事变得很简单：所谓的“cleanup”函数。",
  "We can see this in action by adding a cleanup function to our effect that logs the <code>id</code> that the effect is associated with.": "我们给 effect 加一个 cleanup 函数，并在其中打印它所关联的 <code>id</code>，就能看到它的效果。",
  "Notice that the cleanup function is only called for <code>id</code>s that are no longer relevant. This makes sense because the cleanup function for the most recent effect won't be called until either <em metastring=\"\">another</em> effect runs (making it stale) or the component has been removed from the DOM (irrelevant in this scenario).": "注意 cleanup 函数只会为那些“已经不相关”的 <code>id</code> 被调用。这合乎情理，因为最近一次 effect 的 cleanup 函数要么在<em metastring=\"\">另一次</em>新的 effect 运行（让它变得过期）时调用，要么在组件被从 DOM 中移除时调用（本场景里不会出现）。",
  "We can use this knowledge along with the <span class=\"sparkle_wrapper__cL2jQ\"><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:85%;left:35%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"18\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"18\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:89%;left:76%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"17\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"17\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:73%;left:46%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"13\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"13\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><strong class=\"sparkle_child_wrapper__bem0y\">Power of JavaScript™</strong></span> to fix our problem.": "我们可以把这个规律和 <span class=\"sparkle_wrapper__cL2jQ\"><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:85%;left:35%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"18\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"18\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:89%;left:76%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"17\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"17\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sparkle_sparkle_wrapper__Izdcu\" style=\"top:73%;left:46%\"><svg class=\"sparkle_sparkle_svg__WdZ3Y\" fill=\"none\" height=\"13\" viewbox=\"0 0 68 68\" width=\"13\"><path d=\"M 48 5 L 51 27 L 74 30 L 51 33 L 48 56 L 44 33 L 23 30 L 44 27 Z\" fill=\"var(--yellow)\"></path></svg></span><strong class=\"sparkle_child_wrapper__bem0y\">JavaScript 的力量™</strong></span>结合起来解决问题。",
  "Whenever the effect runs, let's make a variable called <code>ignore</code> and set it to <code>false</code>. Then, whenever the cleanup function runs (which we know will only happen when the effect is stale), we'll set <code>ignore</code> to <code>true</code>.": "每次 effect 运行时，我们创建一个叫 <code>ignore</code> 的变量并把它设为 <code>false</code>。然后每次 cleanup 函数运行时（我们知道这只会发生在 effect 过期时），就把 <code>ignore</code> 设为 <code>true</code>。",
  "Then, all we have to do before we call <code>setPokemon</code> or <code>setError</code>, is check to see if <code>ignore</code> is <code>true</code>. If it is, then we'll do nothing.": "然后，在调用 <code>setPokemon</code> 或 <code>setError</code> 之前，只要检查一下 <code>ignore</code> 是不是 <code>true</code>。如果是，就什么也不做。",
  "Now, regardless of how many times <code>id</code> changes, we'll ignore every response that isn't in the most recent effect. This not only makes our app more performant, but it also improves the UX since React will now only re-render with the latest Pokémon.": "现在不管 <code>id</code> 变了多少次，只要不是最近一次 effect 发出的响应，我们都会忽略。这不仅让应用更高效，也改善了体验 —— React 只会用最新的那只宝可梦触发重新渲染。",
  "You can use the document's <code>visibilitychange</code> event to detect when the page is no longer visible.": "你可以使用 document 的 <code>visibilitychange</code> 事件，来检测页面何时不再可见。",
  "First, let's add some state to track the number of times the employee has tabbed away. We'll call this <code>count</code> and we'll also add some UI for the user to see their count.": "首先，加一块 state 来记录员工切走 tab 的次数。我们叫它 <code>count</code>，再加一点 UI 让用户能看到这个计数。",
  "Now the tricky part. We need to listen for the <code>visibilitychange</code> event and update our <code>count</code> state accordingly. Since we're synchronizing the document's visibility status with our component, we'll use <code>useEffect</code>.": "现在到了棘手的部分。我们需要监听 <code>visibilitychange</code> 事件，并相应地更新 <code>count</code> state。因为是在把 document 的可见性状态与组件同步，所以用 <code>useEffect</code>。",
  "First let's add our event listener. Remember, whenever you add an event listener, you also need to remove it when the component is removed from the DOM or you'll have a memory leak. <code>useEffect</code>'s cleanup function makes this simple.": "先加上事件监听。记住，添加事件监听后，组件从 DOM 移除时你也要记得把它解除掉，否则会造成内存泄漏。<code>useEffect</code> 的 cleanup 函数让这件事变得很简单。",
  "Now all we need to do is update our <code>handleChange</code> function to increment our <code>count</code> state whenever the document is no longer visible. Your first intuition might be to do something like this – where we add <code>count</code> to our dependency array and then increment it by <code>1</code> inside of <code>handleChange</code>.": "现在我们要做的只是更新 <code>handleChange</code>：每当 document 变得不可见时，就让 <code>count</code> 加一。你的第一反应可能是这样写 —— 把 <code>count</code> 加到依赖数组里，然后在 <code>handleChange</code> 里对它 <code>+1</code>。",
  "Whenever the document's <code>visibilityState</code> is no longer visible, we increment <code>count</code> by one. Simple, right? Yes, but actually no. In fact, even though our app appears to be working fine, there's a major problem. Can you spot it?": "每当 document 的 <code>visibilityState</code> 变为不可见时，就把 <code>count</code> 加一。简单吧？看起来是，其实不是。虽然应用看起来工作正常，但这里有一个严重的问题 —— 你能发现吗？",
  "Via our dependency array, we've told React that our effect depends on our <code>count</code> state (which is true). That means, whenever <code>count</code> changes, React will re-render and then, once it's done, re-invoke our effect.": "通过依赖数组，我们告诉了 React：effect 依赖 <code>count</code> state（确实如此）。这意味着每当 <code>count</code> 变化时，React 都会重新渲染，渲染完后再一次调用 effect。",
  "We're in a weird spot. We only want React to add our event listener once, on the initial mount, but we need to include <code>count</code> in the dependency array because we're using it inside of the effect to calculate the new <code>count</code> state.": "我们陷入了一个尴尬的境地。我们只希望 React 在初次挂载时注册一次事件监听，但又必须把 <code>count</code> 放进依赖数组里 —— 因为我们在 effect 内部用它计算新的 <code>count</code>。",
  "What's interesting about this example compared to our other examples is, even though we're using <code>count</code> in the effect, we're not using it as a way to synchronize our component with some external system – so we don't actually need React re-run the effect when it changes.": "这个例子和之前例子有趣的不同之处在于：虽然我们在 effect 里用到了 <code>count</code>，但并不是把它当作“和外部系统同步”的依据 —— 所以我们其实并不需要 React 在它变化时重新运行 effect。",
  "Thankfully, React has a solution for these types of scenarios and it's probably not what you'd expect. In fact, it has nothing to do with <code>useEffect</code> at all. Instead, it has to do with <em metastring=\"\">how</em> we're updating our <code>count</code> state.": "好在 React 对这类场景有一套解决方案，而且很可能不是你预期的那种。事实上它和 <code>useEffect</code> 完全没关系，而是关乎我们<em metastring=\"\">如何</em>更新 <code>count</code> state。",
  "In both of these examples, we're telling React to increment <code>count</code> by <code>1</code>. However, the difference is in how we're getting access to the current state of <code>count</code> before we increment it. In the first example, we're relying on a closure – and therefore we have to specify <code>count</code> inside of the dependency array. In the second, we're not, since React will pass us the current state of <code>count</code> as an argument and therefore, we don't need to include it in the dependency array.": "这两段代码都是告诉 React 把 <code>count</code> 加 <code>1</code>。区别在于：在加一之前，我们是怎么拿到 <code>count</code> 的当前值的。第一种写法依赖闭包 —— 所以必须把 <code>count</code> 放进依赖数组。第二种写法不依赖闭包，因为 React 会把当前的 <code>count</code> 作为参数传给我们，所以就不用把它放进依赖数组了。",
  "With this knowledge, we can now update our example to remove <code>count</code> from the dependency array which prevents React from re-running our effect every time it changes.": "有了这个知识，我们就可以更新示例，把 <code>count</code> 从依赖数组中移除，避免 React 每次它变化时都重新运行 effect。",
  "First is how <code>StrictMode</code> affects <code>useEffect</code>. If you're not familiar, <code>StrictMode</code> is a component that comes with React that allows you to stress test your application in <strong metastring=\"\">development</strong>.": "首先是 <code>StrictMode</code> 对 <code>useEffect</code> 的影响。如果你还不熟悉，<code>StrictMode</code> 是 React 自带的一个组件，用于在<strong metastring=\"\">开发</strong>阶段对应用进行压力测试。",
  "When you have <code>StrictMode</code> \"enabled\" (which is the default for most React apps), React will re-render an <strong metastring=\"\">extra</strong> time, re-run effects an <strong metastring=\"\">extra</strong> time, and check for deprecated APIs.": "当你“启用”了 <code>StrictMode</code>（大多数 React 应用默认都开启），React 会<strong metastring=\"\">额外多</strong>渲染一次、<strong metastring=\"\">额外多</strong>运行一次 effect，并检查是否使用了已废弃的 API。",
  "Why is this helpful? You can think of <code>StrictMode</code> as a stress test of our 3 rules. If render is not pure or you're incorrectly managing side effects, <code>StrictMode</code> will (aggressively) uncover that.": "这有什么好处？你可以把 <code>StrictMode</code> 看作对我们三条规则的压力测试。如果你的 render 不纯、或者副作用管理不当，<code>StrictMode</code> 会（相当激进地）把这些问题暴露出来。",
  "It's controversial, but the whole goal of <code>StrictMode</code> is to make it more obvious that you're doing something wrong – which I think is a reasonable goal. If you stick to the rules we've established, <code>StrictMode</code> will be mostly irrelevant for you.": "虽然有争议，但 <code>StrictMode</code> 的整体目标就是让你更明显地意识到自己做错了什么 —— 我觉得这个目标挺合理的。如果你遵守我们建立的这些规则，<code>StrictMode</code> 基本对你没什么影响。",
  "For more information on it, check out the <a href=\"https://react.dev/reference/react/StrictMode\" metastring=\"\">official documentation</a>.": "想了解更多，可以查看 <a href=\"https://react.dev/reference/react/StrictMode\" metastring=\"\">官方文档</a>。",
  "Throughout our discussion on effects, you may have been wondering the distinction between what needs to be included in <code>useEffect</code>'s dependency array and what doesn't. For example, why doesn't <code>localStorage</code>, <code>Number</code>, or <code>setIndex</code> need to be included in our <code>Greeting</code> effect?": "在讨论 effect 的过程中，你可能一直在琢磨：到底什么应该放进 <code>useEffect</code> 的依赖数组、什么不应该？比如，为什么 <code>localStorage</code>、<code>Number</code> 或 <code>setIndex</code> 不需要放进我们的 <code>Greeting</code> effect 的依赖数组？",
  "The reason is because they're not <strong metastring=\"\">reactive</strong> values. Defined, a reactive value is any value that can change between re-renders. Props, state, or any variables defined inside of a component are all reactive values – and therefore, always need to be included in the dependency array if they're used in the effect.": "原因是它们不是<strong metastring=\"\">响应式</strong>值。所谓响应式值（reactive value），是指任何可能在重渲染之间发生变化的值。props、state、以及组件内部定义的任何变量都是响应式值 —— 因此，只要在 effect 中用到了它们，就必须放进依赖数组。",
  "In our example, <code>localStorage</code> and <code>Number</code> are always going to reference the same spot in memory and React guarantees that the <code>setIndex</code> updater function will also always be consistent across renders, meaning all of these are <strong metastring=\"\">non</strong> reactive values.": "在我们的例子里，<code>localStorage</code> 和 <code>Number</code> 永远引用的是内存里相同的位置；React 也保证 <code>setIndex</code> 这个 updater 函数在多次渲染间始终一致，所以它们都是<strong metastring=\"\">非</strong>响应式值。",
  "This makes sense if you think about it. The whole goal of <code>useEffect</code> is to synchronize your component with some outside system. Non reactive values are irrelevant to <code>useEffect</code> because they're never used in the synchronization process.": "细想一下就会明白：<code>useEffect</code> 的全部目标是把组件与外部系统同步起来。非响应式值与 <code>useEffect</code> 无关，因为它们从不参与同步过程。",
  "If not, <button aria-controls=\"radix-:rls:\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>here's a hint.</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button>": "如果没发现，<button aria-controls=\"\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" class=\"Popover_children__8p5Di\" data-state=\"closed\" type=\"button\"><span>这里有个提示。</span> <svg class=\"fill-brand-purple dark:fill-brand-yellow w-2 h-2 b-2 mx-0.5 mb-4\" enable-background=\"new 0 0 455 455\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 0 455 455\" x=\"0\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" y=\"0\"><path d=\"M347.49 227L454.5 165.212 394.508 61.288 287.5 123.077 287.5 0 167.5 0 167.5 123.077 60.492 61.288 0.499 165.212 107.51 227 0.5 288.788 60.492 392.712 167.5 330.923 167.5 455 287.5 455 287.5 330.923 394.508 392.712 454.501 288.788z\"></path></svg></button>"
}